# Structural Review — tau

Date: 2026-04-19

---

## Issue 1 — Cohesion / Size: `App` is a God Object

- **Type**: Cohesion, Complexity
- **Location**: `src/app.rs` (4,759 lines, 213 functions)
- **Problem**: `App` owns and orchestrates everything: conversation history, agent task lifecycle, streaming state, UI mode state (chat / slash / selection / ask-user / login / shell), provider configuration, session persistence, clipboard, compaction triggering, event dispatch, scroll position, completion popups, and authentication flows.
- **Why it matters**: Any feature that touches two of those responsibilities forces changes to `App`. New contributors can't reason about the blast radius of a change. Test setup (`make_app`) is heavyweight and tests are brittle. The file has no obvious ceiling.
- **Concrete fix**: Extract coherent sub-domains into standalone structs:
  - `AgentState` — live-turn tracking, pending tool calls, abort
  - `UiMode` / `InputMode` — chat / slash / selection / ask-user / login / shell state machine
  - `CompletionState` — model fetch, completion items, selection cursor
  - `ProviderManager` — provider list, token refresh, auth flows
  - `SessionManager` — session ID, event log, persistence

  `App` becomes a thin coordinator that holds these structs and routes events to them.

